<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="type material">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Type material examined and taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1781" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Tenthredo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tenthredo gonagra" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gonagra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Tenthredo gonagra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fabricius, 1781. Lectotype ♀ hereby designated, labelled: &quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1781" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Tenthredo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tenthredo gonagra" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gonagra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Tenthredo gonagra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;; &quot;LECTOTYPE 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1781" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Tenthredo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tenthredo gonagra" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gonagra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Tenthredo gonagra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fabricius, 1781 des. SMBlank 2008&quot; [red, printed: paralectotypes labelled in corresponding way], &quot; ZMUC-GISHym 1050&quot;, &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1801" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1781" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus gonager" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gonager">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus gonager</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(F.) [handwritten] det. S.M.Blank 2008 ✓&quot; [printed], &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1801" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1781" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus gonager" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gonager">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus gonager</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fabricius, 1781) M.Heidemaa det.&quot; [printed]. Right flagellomeres 6-7, right hind tarsus missing. Paralectotype 1♀: &quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1781" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Tenthredo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tenthredo gonagra" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gonagra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Tenthredo gonagra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;, &quot; ZMUC-GISHym 1051&quot;. ZMUC.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
The type specimens correspond with 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Zhelochovtsev’s">Zhelochovtsev's</normalizedToken>
definition of 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1801" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1781" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus (Poodolerus) gonager" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gonager" subGenus="Poodolerus">Dolerus (Poodolerus) gonager</taxonomicName>
, which has red knees, superficially pitted lateral mesonotal lobes and backwards directed setae of the parallel-sided ovipositor sheath (similar to 
<bibRefCitation author="Zhelochovtsev, AN" journalOrPublisher="Brill, Leiden" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B199" refString="Zhelochovtsev, AN, 1994. [Translation of the book published in Russian in 1988]. In: Medvedev GS (Ed.) Keys to the Insects of the European Part of the USSR. Volume III Hymenoptera Part VI Symphyta. E.J. Brill, Leiden" title="[Translation of the book published in Russian in 1988]. In: Medvedev GS (Ed.) Keys to the Insects of the European Part of the USSR. Volume III Hymenoptera Part VI Symphyta. E. J." year="1994">Zhelochovtsev 1994</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 165.2, but with some of the longest hairs curved distally).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Eversmann" authorityYear="1847" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus femoratus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femoratus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus femoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Eversmann, 1847. Lectotype ♀ hereby designated, labelled: &quot;Kas[an] 16.V.&quot;, &quot; 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Eversmann" authorityYear="1847" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus femoratus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femoratus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Dolerus femoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Kl.&quot; [with black frames], &quot;DEI-GISHym 30068&quot; [white, printed], &quot;Lectotype 
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1801" authorityName="Eversmann" authorityYear="1847" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Dolerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Dolerus femoratus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femoratus">Dolerus femoratus</taxonomicName>
Eversmann 1847 vide A. Taeger 2014 des.&quot; [red, printed]. In good condition. Belongs to 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. gonager" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="gonager">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. gonager</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Paralectotypes: 2♀ (DEI-GISHym 30069, 30070), are 
<taxonomicName family="Tenthredinidae" genus="D." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="D. puncticollis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="puncticollis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">D. puncticollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Thomson, 1871. All in ZIN.
</paragraph>
